# The repo root is a Docker build context for services whose Dockerfile copies the paylink-chain
# module (for the `replace` directive) plus their own module: proof-validator (work03) and the
# mpesa-adapter CORE (work04). Exclude everything else so the context stays small.

# Sibling backend services / clients / docs those images do not build from.
linkmint-backend/paylink-service/
linkmint-backend/payment-orchestrator/
# Keep adapters/mpesa (the Go core builds from the repo root); exclude any other adapters and the
# Node rail service (it builds from its own context, not the repo root).
adapters/*
!adapters/mpesa/
adapters/mpesa/daraja-service/
apps/
sdks/
docs/
monitoring/
infra/
.claude/
.github/

# VCS, IDE, design files.
.git/
*.pen

# Chain runtime data + node key (not needed to build; never ship secrets).
paylink-chain/data/
**/*.key

# Language caches / build artifacts / coverage.
**/node_modules/
**/.venv/
**/venv/
**/__pycache__/
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/
**/.coverage
**/coverage.out
**/htmlcov/
**/bin/
